I NEED TO BRING THIS BACK TO MY

12:09.437 --> 12:10.271
LAB.

12:10.397 --> 12:11.439
CODY, CHECK IN ON FRANKIE FOR

12:11.565 --> 12:12.315
ME, WILL YOU?

12:12.440 --> 12:14.150
>> SURE THING, DOC.

12:14.275 --> 12:15.485
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

12:15.610 --> 12:18.321
[ ENGINE REVS ]

12:18.446 --> 12:19.822
>> BOULDER.

12:19.947 --> 12:21.866
>> UNDERSTOOD.

12:31.710 --> 12:33.545
>> FASTER, ALL OF YOU.

12:33.670 --> 12:35.880
BEFORE GRIFFIN ROCK BECOMES

12:36.005 --> 12:37.257
GLACIER  ROCK.

12:37.382 --> 12:39.092
I-I'LL BE INSIDE CITY HALL

12:39.217 --> 12:42.095
G-GETTING WARM.

12:42.220 --> 12:44.097
>> WARM IS NOT A BAD IDEA.

12:44.222 --> 12:45.848
ATTENTION ALL, THE SNOW IS

12:45.973 --> 12:47.892
MAKING IT HARD TO GET ANYWHERE.

12:48.017 --> 12:49.561
AND WITH THE TEMPERATURE

12:49.686 --> 12:51.605
DROPPING, I THINK IT'S BEST FOR

12:51.730 --> 12:53.690
EVERYONE TO GET INSIDE CITY HALL

12:53.814 --> 12:55.358
TO WAIT OUT THE BLIZZARD.

12:55.483 --> 12:56.859
KADE, HELP THEM GET SETTLED.

12:56.984 --> 12:58.111
>> CAN'T CODY DO THAT?

12:58.236 --> 12:59.404
>> HE'LL BE ON DISPATCH.

12:59.529 --> 13:01.030
DANI, I NEED AN EYE IN THE SKY.

13:01.155 --> 13:02.657
YOU AND BLADES LOOK FOR TROUBLE

13:02.781 --> 13:04.200
SPOTS -- ANYONE WHO MIGHT NEED

13:04.325 --> 13:05.159
HELP.

13:05.285 --> 13:07.203
IT'S COLD UP THERE, SO STAY LOW.

13:07.328 --> 13:09.414
>> I KNOW A BOT WHO'LL LIKE THAT

13:09.539 --> 13:10.749
CONCEPT JUST FINE.

13:10.873 --> 13:12.250
>> GRAHAM, YOU AND BOULDER PLOW

13:12.375 --> 13:13.501
A PATH BACK TO DOC'S LAB.

13:13.627 --> 13:14.961
MAKE SURE HE GETS THERE IN ONE

13:15.086 --> 13:15.670
PIECE.

13:15.794 --> 13:16.755
>> YES, SIR.

13:16.879 --> 13:18.797
>> CODY, GET THE ComTab FROM

13:18.923 --> 13:22.761
CHASE, AND USE CITY HALL AS H.Q.

13:22.885 --> 13:23.762
LET'S GO, GANG.

13:23.886 --> 13:25.346
CHRISTMAS CAME EARLY, BUT IT

13:25.472 --> 13:27.766
DIDN'T STAY LONG.

13:35.607 --> 13:39.778
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

13:39.902 --> 13:41.321
[  HORNS BLARING  ]

13:41.446 --> 13:43.448
>> DAD, THERE'S A FIVE-CAR

13:43.573 --> 13:45.408
PILEUP BY THE DRIVE-IN.

13:45.533 --> 13:46.409
>>  WE'RE ON IT.

13:46.534 --> 13:48.035
>>  CODY, IT LOOKS LIKE THE

13:48.161 --> 13:49.746
BRIDGE IS TURNING INTO SOLID

13:49.870 --> 13:50.705
ICE.

13:50.829 --> 13:51.623
>> KADE AND HEATWAVE ARE GOING

13:51.748 --> 13:52.831
TO GET SALT FOR THE ROADS.

13:52.957 --> 13:53.792
I'LL SEND THEM OVER.

13:53.916 --> 13:55.168
AND MAYBE YOU SHOULD SHUT DOWN

13:55.293 --> 13:56.419
THE BRIDGE, IN THE MEANTIME.

13:56.544 --> 13:57.504
>>  WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

13:57.629 --> 13:59.046
>> AND DANI, CAN YOU AND BLADES

13:59.172 --> 14:00.507
DO A FLYOVER BY THE RIVER AND

14:00.632 --> 14:01.466
CHECK ON FRANKIE?

14:01.591 --> 14:03.301
>>  JUST SAW HER -- DON'T THINK

14:03.426 --> 14:04.552
YOU NEED TO WORRY.

14:04.678 --> 14:06.554
[ BEEP ]

14:06.680 --> 14:08.765
>>  CODY! I'M GLAD YOU CALLED.

14:08.889 --> 14:10.308
I CHANGED MY MIND.

14:10.433 --> 14:11.810
I LOVE YOUR SNOW.

14:11.934 --> 14:13.353
YOU HAVE TO COME DOWN HERE AND

14:13.478 --> 14:13.978
TRY THIS.

14:14.103 --> 14:15.647
[  LAUGHTER  ]

14:15.772 --> 14:17.940
>> UH, LOVE TO, BUT I'M A LITTLE

14:18.065 --> 14:19.192
BUSY RIGHT NOW.

14:19.317 --> 14:20.610
I'LL LET YOUR DAD KNOW YOU'RE

14:20.735 --> 14:21.611
OKAY.

14:21.736 --> 14:22.737
>>  TELL HIM TO COME DOWN, TOO.

14:22.862 --> 14:24.364
HEY, IF THIS KEEPS UP, WE COUD

14:24.489 --> 14:25.406
SELL HOT CHOCOLATE.

14:25.532 --> 14:27.074
SEE YOU LATER.

14:27.200 --> 14:29.910
>> BYE.

14:30.036 --> 14:34.290
[ ENGINE REVVING ]

14:34.415 --> 14:36.250
>> I WAS JUST THINKING, WOULDN'T

14:36.376 --> 14:38.127
IT BE A GOOD IDEA TO CLOSE  BOTH

14:38.252 --> 14:39.420
ENDS OF THE BRIDGE?

14:39.546 --> 14:44.884
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

14:45.009 --> 14:45.802
>> [ GASPS ]

14:45.926 --> 14:47.679
>> HOW ABOUT I KEEP AN EYE ON

14:47.804 --> 14:49.430
THE OTHER SIDE?

14:55.061 --> 14:56.979
[ WHIRRING ]

15:04.278 --> 15:05.154
>> [ GROANS ]

15:05.279 --> 15:06.656
THIS WILL TAKE QUITE A WHILE TO

15:06.781 --> 15:08.282
PLOW THROUGH -- EVEN FOR YOUR

15:08.408 --> 15:09.116
VEHICLE.

15:09.242 --> 15:10.993
>> BUT NOT FOR MY ROBOT.

15:11.118 --> 15:12.704
BOULDER, TRANSFORM AND DIG.

15:33.725 --> 15:36.018
>> AAH!

15:40.398 --> 15:42.400
>> GRAHAM, CITY HALL'S ROOF IS

15:42.525 --> 15:43.317
CAVING IN.

15:43.443 --> 15:46.654
I'M SENDING YOU PICTURES.

15:46.780 --> 15:48.281
>> LOOKS LIKE AT LEAST FOUR TONS

15:48.406 --> 15:49.282
OF SNOW UP THERE.

15:49.407 --> 15:50.617
THAT ROOF WON'T HOLD MUCH

15:50.742 --> 15:51.409
LONGER.

15:51.534 --> 15:52.452
ARE PEOPLE STILL INSIDE?

15:52.577 --> 15:54.203
>> YEAH. PEOPLE AND ME!

15:54.328 --> 15:55.622
>>  CODY, GET OUT!

15:55.747 --> 15:57.624
GET EVERYBODY OUT NOW!

15:57.749 --> 15:59.125
[ CREAKING ]

15:59.250 --> 16:00.627
>> [ GASPS ]

16:00.752 --> 16:01.836
>> YOU HEARD HIM.

16:01.961 --> 16:03.003
I'M OUT OF HERE!

16:03.129 --> 16:06.382
I MEAN, UH, I'LL LEAD THE WAY.

16:06.507 --> 16:11.345
[ GRUNTING ]

16:11.471 --> 16:15.349
WE'RE TRAPPED!

16:15.475 --> 16:17.017
>> ALL RESCUE TEAMS, REPORT TO

16:17.143 --> 16:17.977
CITY HALL.

16:18.102 --> 16:20.939
THE ROOF'S ABOUT TO COLLAPSE!

16:23.065 --> 16:25.276
[ CROWD GASPING ]

16:25.401 --> 16:26.861
>> AAH!

16:35.829 --> 16:39.165
[ SIREN WAILS ]

16:42.961 --> 16:45.505
>> CODY'S STILL INSIDE?

16:45.630 --> 16:46.673
[ METAL SCREECHING ]

16:46.798 --> 16:48.174
>> AAH!

16:48.299 --> 16:48.675
OW.

16:48.800 --> 16:49.383
>> GO!

16:49.509 --> 16:50.301
>> HURRY!

16:50.426 --> 16:52.637
>> PLEASE VACATE THE PREMISES IN

16:52.762 --> 16:54.180
AN ORDERLY FASHION.

16:54.305 --> 16:56.015
>> AHH -- AAH!

16:56.140 --> 16:57.099
>> CODY, COME ON.

16:57.224 --> 16:58.351
>> WHERE'S BOULDER?

16:58.476 --> 16:59.310
I HAVE AN IDEA.

16:59.435 --> 17:01.145
>> LET'S TALK ABOUT IT OUTSIDE.

17:01.270 --> 17:04.148
>> OH, CODY.

17:04.273 --> 17:05.692
WHAT WERE YOU DOING IN THERE

17:05.817 --> 17:07.067
BESIDES GIVING US A HEART

17:07.193 --> 17:08.068
ATTACK?

17:08.194 --> 17:09.069
>> I WAS TRYING TO GET A BETTER

17:09.195 --> 17:09.988
VIEW OF THE ROOF.

17:10.112 --> 17:11.238
>> WHAT DO YOU NEED TO SEE?

17:11.364 --> 17:12.198
IT'S CAVING IN.

17:12.323 --> 17:13.449
>> IF BOULDER CAN PROP UP THE

17:13.574 --> 17:14.909
CEILING FROM THE INSIDE, IT'LL

17:15.034 --> 17:16.285
GIVE US A CHANCE TO CLEAR THE

17:16.410 --> 17:17.244
SNOW OFF THE ROOF.

17:17.370 --> 17:19.079
>> AND PREVENT ANY MORE DAMAGE.

17:19.205 --> 17:20.206
GREAT IDEA, CODY.

17:20.331 --> 17:23.877
BOULDER.

17:24.002 --> 17:27.505
>> [ GRUNTING ]

17:27.630 --> 17:28.631
>> GET US UP THERE.

17:28.756 --> 17:30.299
THE THREE OF US COULD CLEAN OFF

17:30.424 --> 17:31.509
THAT ROOF IN NO TIME.

17:31.634 --> 17:32.552
>> NO. TOO RISKY.

17:32.677 --> 17:33.928
YOUR WEIGHT COMBINED WITH THE

17:34.053 --> 17:35.179
SNOW -- WAY MORE THAN THE

17:35.304 --> 17:36.180
STRUCTURE CAN HANDLE.

17:36.305 --> 17:37.765
>> MAYBE WE COULD MELT THE SNOW.

17:37.891 --> 17:39.141
YOU KNOW, WITH A GIANT HAIR

17:39.266 --> 17:42.478
DRYER OR SOMETHING.

17:42.603 --> 17:43.980
OR NOT.

17:44.104 --> 17:45.648
>> WHAT WE NEED IS A WAY TO GET

17:45.773 --> 17:47.316
RID OF THE SNOW WITHOUT ACTUALLY

17:47.441 --> 17:48.943
GOING ON THE ROOF, LIKE A GIANT

17:49.068 --> 17:51.779
SNOWBLOWER.

17:51.905 --> 17:53.447
>> WHAT?

17:53.573 --> 17:56.158
IS THERE SOMETHING ON MY CHEEK?

17:58.118 --> 17:59.954
>> READY TO SHAKE THINGS UP A

18:00.079 --> 18:00.872
LITTLE?

18:00.997 --> 18:02.498
>>  I'M NOT SURE I KNOW WHAT

18:02.623 --> 18:03.207
YOU --

18:03.332 --> 18:06.878
[  SCREAMS  ]

18:07.003 --> 18:09.338
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW I COULD DO

18:09.463 --> 18:10.006
THIS.

18:10.130 --> 18:11.090
[ LAUGHS ]

18:11.215 --> 18:13.509
>> [ GRUNTS ]

18:21.809 --> 18:23.519
>> WHOA!

18:23.644 --> 18:27.398
[  Shuddering  ]  DID WE DO IT?

18:27.523 --> 18:29.067
>> WE DID.

18:29.191 --> 18:30.443
BUT NOW WE BETTER GET YOU THAWED

18:30.568 --> 18:32.612
OUT.

18:32.737 --> 18:38.451
>> YOUR SHIFT IS UP, BOULDER.

18:38.576 --> 18:40.494
>> DOC, HOW'S THE REPAIR GOING?

18:40.620 --> 18:41.996
>> CROSS YOUR FINGERS.

18:42.121 --> 18:45.750
[ WHIRRING ]

18:53.257 --> 18:58.972
[ WHIRRING STOPS ]

18:59.097 --> 19:00.306
>> WHOO-HOO!

19:00.431 --> 19:01.307
>> YEAH!

19:01.432 --> 19:02.475
YES! YEAH!

19:02.600 --> 19:03.476
[ RINGING ]

19:03.601 --> 19:05.061
FRANKIE, YOUR DAD DID IT.

19:05.185 --> 19:06.813
SORRY WE HAD TO BREAK UP YOUR

19:06.938 --> 19:07.814
FUN.

19:07.939 --> 19:09.189
>>  UH, THAT'S NOT ALL YOU BROKE

19:09.315 --> 19:10.149
UP.

19:10.274 --> 19:11.818
I JUST INVENTED A NEW SPORT,

19:11.943 --> 19:16.823
AND I'M NOT SO SURE I LIKE IT.

19:16.948 --> 19:19.117
>> DAD, THIS EMERGENCY'S NOT

19:19.241 --> 19:21.702
OVER YET.

19:29.502 --> 19:30.795
>> RESCUE BOTS, ROLL TO THE

19:30.920 --> 19:31.671
RESCUE!

19:31.796 --> 19:32.713
>> DANI, WE NEED BLADES TO

19:32.839 --> 19:34.090
AIRLIFT FRANKIE OUT OF THE

19:34.214 --> 19:34.841
RIVER.

19:34.966 --> 19:35.675
WHAT'S YOUR STATUS?

19:35.800 --> 19:36.634
>> GROUNDED.

19:36.759 --> 19:38.094
BLADES IS STILL ICED UP FROM OUR

19:38.218 --> 19:39.053
LAST FLIGHT.

19:39.178 --> 19:41.430
>> [ GRUNTS ] I'M TRYING, BUT MY

19:41.555 --> 19:43.891
SWASHPLATE JUST WON'T DEFROST.

19:44.017 --> 19:44.684
[ SIREN WAILS ]

19:44.809 --> 19:45.852
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

19:45.977 --> 19:50.230
[ SIREN STOPS ]

19:50.356 --> 19:51.858
>> IF YOU GET A MOMENT, I

19:51.983 --> 19:54.276
WOULDN'T MIND THE HELP.

20:02.660 --> 20:05.663
>> I'M GONNA HIT THAT.

20:11.627 --> 20:17.299
>> [ GRUNTS ]

20:17.424 --> 20:19.301
>> THE HUMAN WORD FOR THAT IS

20:19.426 --> 20:21.721
"WHOO-HOO!"

20:30.270 --> 20:31.814
>> I WOULDN'T WANT TO DO IT

20:31.939 --> 20:36.694
AGAIN, BUT THAT WAS AWESOME!

20:36.819 --> 20:37.820
[ Shivering ] ACCORDING TO

20:37.945 --> 20:39.197
PRACTICALLY EVERY LAW OF PHYSICS

20:39.321 --> 20:40.656
IN NATURE, THAT SHOULD NOT HAVE

20:40.781 --> 20:43.826
WORKED, BUT THANKS.

20:43.951 --> 20:46.495
>> WHERE DID CHASE GO?

20:46.620 --> 20:48.330
>> [ LAUGHS ]

20:48.455 --> 20:50.374
I THINK I UNDERSTAND NOW.

20:54.795 --> 20:56.338
[ DOG BARKS ]

20:56.463 --> 20:59.008
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

20:59.133 --> 21:00.676
>> HA!

21:00.801 --> 21:03.512
[ GRUNTING ]

21:03.637 --> 21:05.848
>> SO, SUMMER IS SUMMER, AND

21:05.973 --> 21:07.850
WINTER IS WINTER -- WHEN

21:07.975 --> 21:09.977
EVERYBODY'S READY FOR IT.

21:10.103 --> 21:11.771
>> LIKE MY DAD SAYS, "THERE'S A

21:11.896 --> 21:13.022
TIME AND A PLACE FOR

21:13.147 --> 21:13.981
EVERYTHING."

21:14.107 --> 21:15.566
AND I THINK THE BEST TIME AND

21:15.691 --> 21:18.903
PLACE IS HERE AND NOW!

21:19.028 --> 21:19.904
>> OH.

21:20.029 --> 21:22.073
>> HA!

21:22.198 --> 21:24.242
[ GROWLS ]

21:24.366 --> 21:27.245
>> WHAT? [ LAUGHS ]

21:27.369 --> 21:29.580
>> WOULD THAT BE AN "OOPS" OR A

21:29.705 --> 21:32.166
"WHOO-HOO"?
